Source: linux-screen-dimmer
Section: utils
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Linux Screen Dimmer Team <example@example.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper (>= 11), dh-python, python3-all, python3-setuptools
Standards-Version: 4.1.3
Homepage: https://github.com/example/linux-screen-dimmer
X-Python3-Version: >= 3.6

Package: linux-screen-dimmer
Architecture: all
Depends: ${python3:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, python3-gi, gir1.2-gtk-3.0, gir1.2-appindicator3-0.1
Description: Reduce screen brightness beyond hardware limits
 Linux Screen Dimmer provides a way to reduce screen brightness
 beyond hardware limits by creating a transparent overlay.
 Features include system tray control, multi-monitor support,
 and persistent settings.
